name: Minkyu Choi
headline: SWE @ Google
creator: False
bio:
SWE @ Google. 

During my PhD at the University of Michigan, I engage in cutting-edge research at the intersection of Artificial Intelligence and Computational Neuroscience. My goal is to leverage advanced machine learning models to unravel the complexities of data processing in the human brain, aspiring to reach and replicate human efficiency and intelligence. I have published multiple papers in prestigious venues such as NeurIPS and NeuroImage, demonstrating my passion and commitment to advancing the frontiers of machine learning and computational neuroscience.
My expertise encompasses vision foundation models and multimodal foundation models across various domains, such as text, images, fMRI, and physiological data. Some of my notable achievements include: conducting research to enhance multimodal foundation models for medical imaging applications, undertaking projects to align the representations of language models with human understanding, and leading a research initiative to decipher the human visual system. I have also developed AI models for human motion and facial expression synthesis as a Research Intern at Samsung Research America, achieving significant improvements in prediction accuracy and computational efficiency.

I can’t wait to speak with you!
